50|$|The first December 1 {{national}} holiday saw the largest celebrations in Alba Iulia, the location {{in which the}} union of Transylvania with Romania was signed. They were marked by significant political polarization: Corneliu Coposu, then {{the leader of the}} anticommunist opposition, was interrupted several times during a speech by boos from the crowd. Petre Roman, then the prime minister, showed such pleasure at these repeated interruptions that Ion Iliescu had <b>to</b> <b>gesture</b> <b>to</b> <b>him</b> <b>to</b> stop. This signal was captured on filmed and spread widely by the mass media.|$|R
