60|$|A little awed by {{the manner}} of the Commander, Hurlstone bowed and {{followed}} him across the courtyard. It was filled with soldiers, and near the gateway a double file of dragoons, with loaded carbines, were standing at ease. Two sentries were ranged on each side of an open door which gave upon the courtyard. The Commander paused before it, and with a <b>gesture</b> invited <b>him</b> <b>to</b> enter. It was a large square apartment, lighted only by the open door and a grated enclosure above it. Seated in his shirtsleeves, before a rude table, Senor Perkins was quietly writing. The shadow of Hurlstone's figure falling across his paper caused <b>him</b> <b>to</b> look up.|$|R
